    <span class="rad-caption-text">As McCullin’s images draw in closer, they show two corpsmen, with Glass holding an IV. As soon as he saw Blaine drop, Glass ran to him and bandaged him with standard-issue field dressings, inserted a drip and spoke to Blaine before he faded out. By contrast, Grantham said his initial first aid was improvised and minimal, with nearby Marines using cellophane from cigarette packets to try to seal his wounds. McCullin’s photo shows a more organized first-aid effort by a pair of corpsmen who had medical equipment on hand.</span>
